node.text: Andrea Navedo....te envidio por los besos de Rogelio....uff😘😘😘😘😘

Had the honor today to hang out and share some of my stories growing up in #nyc with these beautiful young ladies from the Community School for Social Justice in the #Bronx Talking about #womensempowerment, #choice , #selfworth , #metoo , #domesticviolence , #femaleimagesinmedia #janethevirgin and so much more Thank you @lizcondeconde for inviting me! And thank you to the young ladies for taking the time to listen to me 😘😘😘
You’re amazing ❤
I‘m sure you are an inspiration to those girls (and many more). Quite probably I‘m never going to meet you in person but you seem such a kind and loving person, thanks for sharing the things you do
@keep_ahead 😘😘😘
@keep_ahead no matter the color of our hair, or any other creative form of self-expression,  we're beautiful. You look beautiful.
@i_am_evaz  Thank you 🙏🏽😊❤️❤️ofc. We are all beautiful no matter what and i love my hair I actually had it several colors before
Lol look at me and my crazy green hair 😂 I absolutely loved it thank you for giving ur time to come to our school and express ur experiences and thank you for being so bright and kind ur amazing!❤️💛
@alwaysjafael 😘😘😘
Your so inspiring! I love you so much and you have taught me and others so much through your posts. Your my role model and some one I look up to every day♥️😭
Xooo lyyy
I dead live in the Bronx I wished I seen you
Thanks for stopping by and speaking with our girls! It means so much to all of us. 💕
Why are you so amazing 👏
@andreanavedo  I work with our youth in high schools - I'm a social worker. Our kids need strong role models like you. It warms my heart to know that you took the time to visit with them.

@marielaherbo Mamá being pregnant is not easy but millions have done it before and have been able to keep doing what they need to do especially because they have a baby on the way. Don’t let being pregnant stop you, let it motivate you instead to work harder and do your best because it’s not just about you anymore. Wishing you all the best but know that everyday you can make a choice to do better. Go on YouTube and watch @lisa2motivate speeches. She talks about what she went through as she was raising her son on government assistance. She is now the ceo of a multi million dollar company. Keep your head up and be proud. You got this! 💗💗💗
@andreanavedo thanks that was really inspiring coming from a powerful women like you and jean the virgin is the best show I love it 😍😍😍
I go to that school to but I’m pregnant so I can’t do much 😞
@yktv.flacka Thank you mama!!! 😘
i ain't get a picture wit you but i loved ya speech & iloveyou❤
